cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CY 

The paper proposes a new framework for reinforcement learning algorithms that output policy certificates, which can be used to ensure accountability and intervention in high-stakes applications like healthcare. This involves theoretical analysis and the introduction of two new algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also involves some aspects of control theory, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of accountability, which could be relevant to the sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society).
